			<link>http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?75720-September-13-Release-Thread&amp;goto=newpost</link>
			<pubDate>Sun, 01 Sep 2013 03:13:34 GMT</pubDate>
			<description><![CDATA[September doesn't have as many releases as August did, but it has it has one of the biggest hitters of the year to make up for it. 
 
That's right, the big game this month is *Grand Theft Auto V*, and the hype train is in full swing. And while I do think people are overhyping it, I also think it's...]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>September doesn't have as many releases as August did, but it has it has one of the biggest hitters of the year to make up for it.<br />
<br />
That's right, the big game this month is <b>Grand Theft Auto V</b>, and the hype train is in full swing. And while I do think people are overhyping it, I also think it's probably going to be a great game. Better combat, a bigger world, three characters, etc etc. Even the multiplayer sounds very well thought out. It unlocks two weeks after launch to give everyone a chance to play through the main game first (a smart idea in my opinion). You create a character, join a guild, play missions with friends, or just screw around. They claim the world is persistent for 16 players but haven't gone into specifics. <br />
<br />
After GTA5, the biggest release might be <b>Total War: Rome II</b> for you PC guys. I haven't really seen anyone talking about it, but the series has a good pedigree. <br />
<br />
If you own a Wii U but no games for it, <b>The Wonderful 101</b> comes out this month (it's already out in Europe I believe). Platinum games make the best games that no one buys, give it a shot if you have a Wii U. Sort of an action oriented Pikmin style game. Supposed to be fairly challenging. While it's supposedly good on any platform, <b>Rayman Legends</b> is also due this month, and makes better use of the Wii U's tablet than many Nintendo games.<br />
<br />
If it's Sony games you are after, the Vita gets <b>Killzone: Mercenary</b>, and the PS3 gets a $40 budget platformer by the name of <b>Puppeteer</b> which has gotten a fair amount of positive attention. I think it would be amazing if $40 became the standard for all games of the last generation from this point forward. The PS3 port of KH: Final Mix (a Japanese only re-release of the first game) <b>Kingdom Hearts HD 1.5 Remix</b> is also only $40 this month.<br />
<br />
Finally, while I don't really expect anyone here to care, <b>Diablo III</b> is set to make its console debut and a HD remake of Mickey Mouse's <b>Castle of Illusion</b> is also set to be released this month.<br />
<br />
