			<title>Hearthstone - is anyone following this?</title>
			<link>http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?75693-Hearthstone-is-anyone-following-this&amp;goto=newpost</link>
			<pubDate>Mon, 26 Aug 2013 21:21:31 GMT</pubDate>
			<description><![CDATA[It's a Magic: the Gathering-style game that Blizzard is making, using WoW characters and ideas. Here's MMO-Champ's site for discussion: 
 
http://www.hearthpwn.com/ 
 
It's in beta right now, no NDA on anyone, at some point in the future it'll enter open beta where anyone who wants in can get in....]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>It's a Magic: the Gathering-style game that Blizzard is making, using WoW characters and ideas. Here's MMO-Champ's site for discussion:<br />
<br />
<a href="http://www.hearthpwn.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">http://www.hearthpwn.com/</a><br />
<br />
It's in beta right now, no NDA on anyone, at some point in the future it'll enter open beta where anyone who wants in can get in. I'm hoping to get in the next wave of invites on Tuesday, because I loved playing Magic back in the day and the game does look interesting. Mostly, I want to see if one can play the game without a significant outlay of cash for cards. There seems to be mechanics to allow for it (&quot;daily quests&quot; that award gold, which can be used to buy cards; the Arena, a pack draft environment that gives out big prizes; you can disenchant cards and create cards with the resulting dust), but it's a question of how far those mechanics go. If I could play and enjoy myself without paying more than a standard MMO sub price per month, I think I'd get the game.<br />
<br />
So has anyone else been following the game at all?</div>

]]></content:encoded>
