			<title>Games for Windows Live to be shut down</title>
			<link>http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?75661-Games-for-Windows-Live-to-be-shut-down&amp;goto=newpost</link>
			<pubDate>Tue, 20 Aug 2013 10:11:58 GMT</pubDate>
			<description>Microsoft announced (sortof) that as of July 1, 2014, they will be shutting down the GFWL servers. I have not heard if they plan to replace it with something else. The information was on a support page for Age of Empires Online, although it has apparently been taken down. 
 
I gave GFWL the benefit...</description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>Microsoft announced (sortof) that as of July 1, 2014, they will be shutting down the GFWL servers. I have not heard if they plan to replace it with something else. The information was on a support page for Age of Empires Online, although it has apparently been taken down.<br />
<br />
I gave GFWL the benefit of the doubt for awhile, but even I am fed up with it by this point. Microsoft gave up on PCs years ago, and it's about time they stop making us suffer just to they could pretend to care.<br />
<br />
I just hope the games that currently use it can have it patched out. Seeing as how you have to go through an awkward log-in process just to play most of them, it would suck for them to simply become unplayable.</div>

