			<description><![CDATA[Gamescon has always seemed a little more PC centric to me, but this year both Microsoft and Sony have a presence as they build up towards their new console launches. I figure we could use a new thread for anything new announced. Feel free to post anything interesting from Gamescon that doesn't...]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div>Gamescon has always seemed a little more PC centric to me, but this year both Microsoft and Sony have a presence as they build up towards their new console launches. I figure we could use a new thread for anything new announced. Feel free to post anything interesting from Gamescon that doesn't involve them as well, but most publishers seem to just rehash old material so I'm not expecting much.<br />
<br />
Sony has a conference later today that I believe will be streamed. I'm expecting at least one new exclusive, and probably some new info on stuff like The Order. <br />
<br />
Microsoft's thing is going on now, but they decided not to stream it, so news is just coming in bits and pieces. A lot of their stuff was also leaked ahead of time, like Microsoft turning the console itself into a dev kit and allowing indie's to self publish.<br />
<br />
So far all I've heard is that they are making a new Fable (surprise surprise) with 4 player co-op, and that FIFA will be included in all European pre-orders.</div>

